---
import Base from "../../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PageTitle from "../../../components/PageTitle.astro";
import CTA from "../../../components/CTA.astro";

const locale = "en";
const title = "Create your provider accounts";
const intro = "A typical catena deployment leans on a handful of external accounts that stay in your name. Walk through what you can; we will cover the rest together at the install meeting.";
---
<Base
  locale={locale}
  title={title}
  description="Step-by-step: create the external provider accounts (Cloudflare, Tailscale, OVH, eazybackup, SMTP) that a typical catena deployment needs."
>
  <PageTitle title={title} intro={intro} />

  <article class="guide">
    <div class="container">
      <ol>
        <li>
          <h2>Email provider: choose one</h2>
          <p>
            Catena does not host email; it integrates with the
            provider you pick. Open the
            <a href="/en/guides/email-providers/">email provider comparison</a>
            and choose one of the six we recommend (Migadu,
            Mailbox.org, Hostpoint, Infomaniak, OVH Pro Mail,
            Mailfence), then create the account in your business
            name. Pick the
            mailbox plan that matches your team size; we wire the
            DNS records and the transactional sender for you at
            install.
          </p>
          <p class="muted">Time: 15-30 minutes (account creation + initial domain verification).</p>
          <p class="resources">
            <a class="screenshot" href="/img/guides/provider-accounts/email.en.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              <img src="/img/guides/provider-accounts/email.en.png" alt="Email provider selection walkthrough screenshot" loading="lazy" />
            </a>
            <a class="docs-link" href="/en/guides/email-providers/">
              Compare the six providers &rarr;
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <h2>Cloudflare: create an API key</h2>
          <p>
            <a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com/sign-up" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sign up</a>
            with the email address you want on the invoice and add
            your business domain to Cloudflare DNS (free tier is
            enough). Then create an API token scoped to your zone
            so the install can publish DNS records and the public
            tunnel on your behalf.
          </p>
          <p class="muted">Time: 10-15 minutes (DNS propagation).</p>
          <p class="resources">
            <a class="screenshot" href="/img/guides/provider-accounts/cloudflare.en.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              <img src="/img/guides/provider-accounts/cloudflare.en.png" alt="Cloudflare API token walkthrough screenshot" loading="lazy" />
            </a>
            <a class="docs-link" href="https://developers.cloudflare.com/fundamentals/api/get-started/create-token/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Full Cloudflare docs &rarr;
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <h2>Tailscale: create an OAuth client ID</h2>
          <p>
            <a href="https://login.tailscale.com/start" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Start a tailnet</a>
            using SSO from your existing email provider (Google,
            Microsoft, GitHub). Then create an OAuth client so the
            install can add the new server to your private network
            without you sharing a personal login.
          </p>
          <p class="muted">Time: 5-10 minutes.</p>
          <p class="resources">
            <a class="screenshot" href="/img/guides/provider-accounts/tailscale.en.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              <img src="/img/guides/provider-accounts/tailscale.en.png" alt="Tailscale OAuth client walkthrough screenshot" loading="lazy" />
            </a>
            <a class="docs-link" href="https://tailscale.com/kb/1215/oauth-clients" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Full Tailscale docs &rarr;
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <h2>OVH (or another VPS provider): rent a VPS</h2>
          <p>
            <a href="https://www.ovhcloud.com/en-ca/vps/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Create an OVH account</a>
            and order a VPS in your name. Not sure which size fits
            your team? See the
            <a href="/docs/sizing/">sizing guide</a>
            for a quick recommendation by headcount and workload.
            Beauharnois (Quebec) is the default region so your data
            stays in Canada.
          </p>
          <p class="muted">Time: 30 minutes (account verification can stretch on first sign-up).</p>
          <p class="resources">
            <a class="screenshot" href="/img/guides/provider-accounts/ovh.en.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              <img src="/img/guides/provider-accounts/ovh.en.png" alt="OVH VPS order walkthrough screenshot" loading="lazy" />
            </a>
            <a class="docs-link" href="https://help.ovhcloud.com/csm/en-ca-vps-getting-started?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0047708" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Full OVH docs &rarr;
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <h2>eazybackup: create immutable S3 backup storage</h2>
          <p>
            <a href="https://eazybackup.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open an eazybackup account</a>
            and create an S3-compatible bucket with Object Lock and
            versioning turned on. eazybackup is Canadian-owned and
            runs in Ottawa, so your offsite backups stay in Canada
            and cannot be silently overwritten or deleted.
          </p>
          <p class="muted">Time: 15 minutes.</p>
          <p class="resources">
            <a class="screenshot" href="/img/guides/provider-accounts/eazybackup.en.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              <img src="/img/guides/provider-accounts/eazybackup.en.png" alt="eazybackup signup walkthrough screenshot" loading="lazy" />
            </a>
            <a class="docs-link" href="https://eazybackup.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Full eazybackup docs &rarr;
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <h2>SMTP relay: configure a sender for automated email</h2>
          <p>
            Catena does not run a mail server; it relays automated
            email (password resets, calendar invites, ticket
            notifications) through a sender of your choice. Default:
            <a href="https://resend.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Resend</a>
            (one-click setup — add your domain, drop the DNS records
            into Cloudflare, generate an API key). Alternatives:
            <a href="https://www.brevo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Brevo</a>
            (generous free tier), or your existing transactional-email
            provider.
          </p>
          <p class="muted">Time: 10-20 minutes with Resend (DNS verification round-trip).</p>
          <p class="resources">
            <a class="screenshot" href="/img/guides/provider-accounts/resend.en.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              <img src="/img/guides/provider-accounts/resend.en.png" alt="Resend domain + API key walkthrough screenshot" loading="lazy" />
            </a>
            <a class="docs-link" href="https://resend.com/docs/dashboard/domains/introduction" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Full Resend docs &rarr;
            </a>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="closing">
        The further you get through this list, the faster the
        install meeting goes. If you only have time to create the
        accounts before we meet, that is fine too: we will walk
        through every step together on the call.
      </p>
      <p class="back">
        <a href="/en/guides/">&larr; All guides</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <CTA locale={locale} />
</Base>

<style>
  .guide { padding-bottom: var(--catena-space-16); }
  .guide :global(.container) { max-width: var(--catena-content-narrow); }
  ol {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: step;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--catena-space-12) 0;
  }
  ol > li {
    counter-increment: step;
    padding: var(--catena-space-6) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--catena-surface-border);
  }
  ol > li:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
  ol > li::before {
    content: counter(step);
    display: inline-block;
    width: 1.75rem;
    height: 1.75rem;
    line-height: 1.75rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-right: var(--catena-space-3);
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--catena-accent);
    color: white;
    font-weight: var(--catena-fw-semibold);
    font-size: var(--catena-fs-sm);
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  ol > li h2 {
    display: inline;
    font-size: var(--catena-fs-xl);
  }
  ol > li p {
    margin: var(--catena-space-3) 0 0 0;
    line-height: var(--catena-lh-relaxed);
  }
  .closing {
    margin-top: var(--catena-space-8);
    line-height: var(--catena-lh-relaxed);
    color: var(--catena-surface-fg-muted);
  }
  .back { margin-top: var(--catena-space-8); font-size: var(--catena-fs-sm); }
  .resources {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--catena-space-4);
    margin-top: var(--catena-space-4);
  }
  .resources .screenshot {
    display: inline-block;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    max-width: 240px;
    border: 1px solid var(--catena-surface-border);
    border-radius: var(--catena-radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
    line-height: 0;
  }
  .resources .screenshot img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }
  .resources .docs-link {
    font-size: var(--catena-fs-sm);
    font-weight: var(--catena-fw-medium);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
</style>
